text: Alsodes kaweshkari is a frog. It lives in Chile. ==Home== This frog lives in cold places with no trees and in forests. People find it under logs Scientists saw the frog between 1500 and 3000 meters above sea level. Scientists saw the frog one protected place: Bernardo O'Higgins National Park. ==Young== Scientists think the tadpoles swim in streams. ==Threats== Scientists do not know whether this frog is in danger of dying out. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Alsodes kaweshkari
